                            <h3><b>Anterior Deltoid</b></h3><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Your </span><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537056/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">shoulders</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> are made up of three muscle groups; your anterior deltoids, lateral deltoids, and posterior deltoids. Your anterior deltoids are located at the front of your shoulders.</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">As a secondary mover, your anterior deltoids largely play a stabilizing role. As your arms come together, they stabilize your shoulder joints to maintain a controlled movement. </span></p>                        </div>
